obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (3049)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3049&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Kalakshetra Foundation`
  line `Act, 1993.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 29th day of September, 1993.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (3050)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration of Kalakshetra as an institution of national importance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3050&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `Whereas the objects of`
  line `the institution known as Kalakshetra at Adyar, Madras in the State of Tamil Nadu, founded by the late`
  line `Thirumathi Rukmini Devi Arundale, are such as to make the institution one of national importance, it is`
  line `hereby declared that the institution known as Kalakshetra is an institution of national importance.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (3051)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3051&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Academic Committee" means the Academic Committee constituted under section 15;`
  line
  line `(b) "appointed day" means the date on which the Foundation is established under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 8;`
  line
  line `(c) "Board of Trustees" means the Board of Trustees managing the affairs of Kalakshetra under`
  line `the "scheme writ" approved by the Madras High Court in petition No. 716 of 1985;`
  line
  line `(d) "constituent units means the units of Kalakshetra specified in the First Schedule;`
  line
  line `(e) "Director" means the Director appointed under sub-section (1) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(f) "Finance Committee" means the Finance Committee constituted under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 17;`
  line
  line `(g) "Foundation" means the Kalakshetra Foundation established under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 8;`
  line
  line `(h) "Fund" means the Fund of the Foundation referred to in section 22;`
  line
  line `(i) "Governing Board" means the Governing Board constituted under section 11;`
  line
  line `(j) "Kalakshetra" means the institution known as Kalakshetra founded by the late Thirumathi`
  line `Rukmini Devi Arundale, situated at Adyar, Madras, and includes its constituent units;`
  line
  line `(k) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(l) "Member" means a Member of the Governing Board and includes the Chairperson thereof;`
  line
  line `(m) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(n) "regulations" means regulations made under section 32;`
  line
  line `(o) "Schedule" means a Schedule annexed to this Act;`
  line
  line `(p) "State Government" means the Government of Tamil Nadu.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (3052)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Transfer to, and vesting in, the Central Government of the assets and properties of Kalakshetra.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3052&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `On the commencement of this Act, the right, title and interest in relation to the assets and`
  line `properties of Kalakshetra specified in the Second Schedule and vested in the Board of Trustees or any`
  line `other body, in whatever capacity, shall Stand transferred to, and vest in, the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (3053)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `General effect of vesting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3053&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The right, title and interest vested in the Central Government under`
  line `section 4 shall be deemed to include all the assets, rights, leaseholds, powers, authorities, licences and`
  line `privileges; all property (movable and immovable) including lands and buildings; musical instruments;`
  line `equipments used in teaching, training and staging of performing arts; tools and facilities used in arts and`
  line `crafts; costumes and decorative items; books; stationery, furniture and other equipments used in libraries`
  line `and laboratories; works of art and artefacts; stores, automobiles and other vehicles; workshops;`
  line `cash balances, funds including reserve funds, investments and all other rights and interests arising out of`
  line `such assets and properties as were immediately before the commencement of this Act in the possession`
  line `ownership, power or control of the Board of Trustees or any other body, in whatever capacity, and all`
  line `books of account, registers, maps, plans and all other documents of whatever nature relating thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) All assets and properties as aforesaid which have vested in the Central Government under section 4`
  line `shall, by force of such vesting, be freed and discharged from any trust, obligation, mortgage, charge, lien`
  line `and all other encumbrances affecting them or of any attachment, injunction, decree or order of any court or`
  line `other authority restricting the use of such assets or properties in any manner, or appointing any receiver in`
  line `respect of the whole or any part of such assets and properties shall be deemed to have been withdrawn.`
  line
  line `(3) Any licence, permission, authority, concession, facility, privilege, affiliation or any other`
  line `instrument of similar nature granted to the Board of Trustees or any other body, in whatever capacity, in`
  line `relation to the assets and properties of Kalakshetra or any of its constituent units which has vested in the`
  line `Central Government under section 4, at any time before the commencement of this Act and in force`
  line `immediately before such commencement, shall continue to be in force on and after such commencement in`
  line `accordance with its tenor in relation to, and for purposes of, such assets and properties, or where the`
  line `direction under section 6 has been issued, the Foundation shall be deemed to be substituted in such`
  line `licence, permission, authority, concession, facility, privilege affiliation or other instrument, as if it had`
  line `been granted to the Foundation and the Foundation shall hold it for the remainder of the period for which`
  line `the Board of Trustees or any other body, in whatever capacity, would have held it under the terms thereof.`
  line
  line `(4) If, on the commencement of this Act, any suit, appeal or other proceeding of whatever nature in`
  line `relation to any assets or properties which have vested in the Central Government under section 4,`
  line `instituted or preferred by the Board of Trustees is pending, the same shall not abate, be discontinued or`
  line `be, in any way, prejudicially affected by reason of such transfer and vesting, or of anything contained in`
  line `this Act, but the suit, appeal or other proceeding may be continued, prosecuted or enforced, by the Central`
  line `Government or where the right, title and interest in relation to such assets and properties are directed`
  line `under section 6 to vest in the Foundation, by the Foundation.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (3054)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Central Government to direct vesting of assets and properties in the Foundation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3054&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 4 and 5, the Central Government shall`
  line `direct, by notification, that the right, title and interest in relation to the assets and properties of`
  line `Kalakshetra, which had vested in it under section 4, shall vest in the Foundation on such date, not being a`
  line `date earlier than the date of commencement of this Act, as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) On and from the date of vesting of the right, title and interest in relation to the assets, and`
  line `properties of Kalakshetra in the Foundation under sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) the Foundation shall be deemed to have become the owner of the assets and properties; and`
  line
  line `(b) the rights and liabilities of the Central Government, in relation to such assets and properties`
  line `shall be deemed to have become the rights and liabilities respectively of the Foundation.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (3055)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Duty of persons to deliver and to account for assets, properties, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3055&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the vesting in the`
  line `Central Government of the assets and properties of Kalakshetra, all persons in charge of the managementof the said assets and properties immediately before the date of such vesting, shall be bound to deliver to`
  line `the Central Government or to the Foundation or to such person or body of persons as the Central`
  line `Government or the Foundation may specify in this behalf, all assets, properties, books of account, registers`
  line `or other, documents in their custody relating to the assets and properties of Kalakshetra.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person who has, in his possession or control any assets, properties, books, documents or`
  line `other papers relating to Kalakshetra which have vested in the Central Government or the Foundation under`
  line `this Act, and which belong to, Kalakshetra or would have so belonged if Kalakshetra had not vested in the`
  line `Central Government or the Foundation, shall be liable to account for the said assets, properties, books,`
  line `documents and other papers to the Central Government or the Foundation, as the case may be, and shall`
  line `deliver them up to the Central Government or the Foundation or to such person or body of persons as the`
  line `Central Government or the Foundation may specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall take or cause to be taken all necessary steps for securing possession`
  line `of assets and properties of Kalakshetra which have vested in it under section 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (3056)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Establishment and incorporation of Foundation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3056&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, appoint in this behalf there shall be established a Foundation to be`
  line `called the Kalakshetra Foundation.`
  line
  line `(2) The Foundation shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and`
  line `a common seal, with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property, both movable and immovable, and to`
  line `contract and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The office of the Foundation shall be located at Thiruvanmiyur, Madras.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (3057)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `The objects of Foundation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3057&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The objects of the Foundation shall be,--`
  line
  line `(i) to emphasise the essential unity of all true arts;`
  line
  line `(ii) to work for the recognition of the arts as vital to the individual, national and international`
  line growth;
  line
  line `(iii) to maintain the highest traditions of art and culture in their pristine purity and in conformity`
  line `with traditions;`
  line
  line `(iv) to arrange for the training, research, study, teaching and development of art and science,`
  line `music, dance-drama, fine arts, and Bharat-Natyam; and`
  line
  line `(v) to ensure that the principles of "education without fear" and "art without vulgarity" are`
  line `adhered to in the activities of the Foundation and not to permit any deviation from these high ideals`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (3058)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Authorities of the Foundation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3058&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Foundation shall consist of the following, authorities,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Governing Board;`
  line
  line `(b) the Academic Committee; and`
  line
  line `(c) the Finance Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) In the discharge of functions and exercise of powers under this Act, the authorities referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be guided by the objects specified in section 9.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (3059)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `The Governing Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3059&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The Governing Board shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson, who shall be a person of high eminence in public life, to be appointed by the`
  line `Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) not more than twelve Members to be nominated by the Central Government from amongst`
  line `persons who--`
  line
  line `(i) have rendered valuable service to Kalakshetra;`
  line
  line `(ii) have been connected with, or have knowledge of art, culture, folk arts and crafts;`
  line
  line `(iii) are eminent artistes; and`
  line
  line `(iv) are patrons of art and culture;`
  line
  line `(c) two persons, possessing one or more of the qualifications referred to in sub-clauses (i) to (iv) of`
  line `clause (b), to be nominated by the State Government;`
  line
  line `(d) two officers of the Central Government, not below the rank of a Deputy Secretary, to be`
  line `nominated by that Government, to represent the Ministry of the Central Government dealing with`
  line `culture, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) one officer of the State Government, not below the rank of Joint Secretary, to be nominated by`
  line `that Government, to represent the Department of Education of that Government, ex officio; and`
  line
  line `(f) the Director, ex officio.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (3060)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Term of office of Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3060&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The term of office of the Members shall be five years from the`
  line `date of constitution of the Governing Board.`
  line
  line `(2) If a casual vacancy occurs in the office of a Member nominated under clause (b) or clause (c) of`
  line `section 11, whether by reason of his death, resignation or inability to discharge his functions owing to`
  line `illness or other incapacity, such vacancy shall be filled by making fresh nomination and the Member so`
  line `nominated shall hold office for the remainder of the term of office of the Member in whose place he is so`
  line nominated.
  line
  line `(3) An outgoing, Member shall be eligible for re-nomination.`
  line
  line `(4) A Member may resign his office by writing under his hand addressed to the Central Government`
  line `but shall continue in office until his resignation is accepted by that Government.`
  line
  line `(5) The Members nominated under clauses (b) and (c) of section 11, shall be entitled to such`
  line `allowances as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (3061)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Meetings of the Governing Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3061&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Governing Board shall meet at least twice in a year at`
  line `Madras at such time as may be fixed by the Chairperson of the Governing Board.`
  line
  line `(2) All decisions at the meeting of the Governing Board shall be taken by majority of the Members`
  line `present and voting:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of equality of votes the Chairperson of the Governing Board shall have a`
  line `casting vote.`
  line
  line `(3) The Governing Board shall observe such procedure in regard to the transaction of its business at its`
  line `meetings (including the quorum at its meetings) as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(4) No act or proceeding of the Governing Board shall be invalid merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Governing Board; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the nomination of a person acting as a Member of the Governing Board; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Governing Board not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (3062)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Governing Board to be the supreme authority of Foundation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3062&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Governing Board shall`
  line `be the supreme authority of the Foundation and the general superintendence, direction and management of`
  line `the affairs of the Foundation shall vest in the Governing Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Governing Board shall exercise such powers and discharge such functions as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (3063)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Academic Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3063&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Academic Committee shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) the Director;`
  line
  line `(b) the Heads of the constituent units;`
  line
  line `(c) three distinguished persons in the field of art and culture including dance, music, folk arts and`
  line `crafts, to be nominated by the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(d) one person to be nominated by the State Government, representing the Department of`
  line `Education of that Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The tenure of office and other terms and conditions of the members of the Academic Committee`
  line `shall be such as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) The Academic Committee shall observe such procedure in regard to the transaction of its business`
  line `at its meetings (including the quorum at the meetings) as may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (3064)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Powers and functions of Academic Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3064&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Academic Committee shall be responsible`
  line `for the maintenance of standards of education, training and examination conducted by the constituent units`
  line `and shall exercise such other powers and perform such other functions as may be assigned to it, from time`
  line `to time, by the Governing Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (3065)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Finance Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3065&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Finance Committee shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) the Financial Adviser to the Government of India or his nominee in the Ministry of the Central`
  line `Government dealing with culture;`
  line
  line `(b) an officer of the Central Government, not below the rank of a Deputy Secretary, to be`
  line `nominated by that Government;`
  line
  line `(c) an officer of the State Government not below the rank of a Deputy Secretary, to be nominated`
  line `by that Government, representing the Department of Finance of that Government; and`
  line
  line `(d) the Director.`
  line
  line `(2) The Finance Committee shall observe such procedure in regard to the transaction of the business at`
  line `its meetings as may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (3066)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Powers and functions of Finance Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3066&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Finance Committee shall--`
  line
  line `(i) scrutinise the annual statement of accounts and budget estimates of the Foundation prepared by`
  line `the Director and make recommendations to the Governing Board;`
  line
  line `(ii) prescribe the limits of the recurring and non-recurring expenditure of the Foundation for each`
  line `financial year;`
  line
  line `(iii) review the financial position of the Foundation from time to time and have an internal audit`
  line `conducted; and`
  line
  line `(iv) perform such other functions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (3067)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Appointment and duties of Director.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3067&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by notification,`
  line `appoint a Director who shall be the principal executive officer of the Foundation and who shall be`
  line `responsible for the proper administration of the affairs of the Foundation and its day-to-day management`
  line `and shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be assigned to him by the`
  line `Governing Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director shall prepare the annual statement of accounts and budget estimates of the`
  line `Foundation for scrutiny by the Finance Committee.`
  line
  line `(3) The Director shall be a whole time employee of the Foundation and shall be entitled to such salary`
  line `and allowances out of the Fund and shall be subject to such conditions of service in respect of leave,`
  line `pension, provident fund and other matters, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (3068)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Transfer of service of existing employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3068&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, every officer or`
  line `other employee, employed immediately before the appointed day in connection with the affairs of`
  line `Kalakshetra shall become an officer or other employee of the Foundation and shall hold office by the same`
  line `tenure and remuneration and on the same terms and conditions as to pension, gratuity and other matters as`
  line `he would have held under the Board of Trustees or any other body, in whatever, capacity, if this Act had`
  line `not been passed and shall continue to do so, unless and until his employment in the Foundation is terminated or until his tenure, remuneration and other terms and conditions are duly altered by the`
  line `Foundation:`
  line
  line `Provided that the tenure, remuneration and other terms and conditions of service of any such officer`
  line `or employee shall not be altered to his disadvantage without the previous approval of the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (3069)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Grants by Central Government to the Foundation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3069&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of enabling the`
  line `Foundation to discharge its functions efficiently under this Act, the Central Government may, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Foundation in each financial year, such`
  line `sums of money, on such terms and conditions as that Government may determine, by way of grant, loan or`
  line otherwise.
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (3070)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Fund of the Foundation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3070&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Foundation shall have its own Fund; and all sums which may,`
  line `from time to time, be paid to it by the Central Government and all receipts of the Foundation (including`
  line `any sum to which the State Government or any other authority or person may pay to the Foundation) shall`
  line `be credited to the Fund and all payments by the Foundation shall be made therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) All moneys belonging to the Fund shall be deposited in such banks or invested in such manner as`
  line `may, subject to the approval of the Central Government, be decided by the Governing Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The Foundation may spend such sums as it may think fit for performing its functions under this`
  line `Act, and such sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out of the Fund of the Foundation.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (3071)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3071&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The Foundation shall prepare, in such form and at such time each year, as may be`
  line `prescribed, the budget in respect of the financial year next ensuring showing the estimated receipts and`
  line `expenditure, and copies thereof shall be forwarded to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (3072)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Accounts and audit of the Foundation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3072&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Foundation shall maintain proper accounts and`
  line `other relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts including the balance sheet in such`
  line `form as may be approved by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Foundation shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line `and any expenditure incurred by him in connection with such audit shall be payable by the Foundation to`
  line `the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the Foundation shall have the same rights, privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India has in connection with the`
  line `audit of the Government accounts, and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of`
  line `books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect the office of the`
  line Foundation.
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Foundation as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or`
  line `any person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (3073)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Duty to furnish returns, annual reports, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3073&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Foundation shall furnish to the Central`
  line `Government at such time and in such form and in such manner, as may be prescribed, or as the Central`
  line `Government may direct, such returns and statements and such particulars in regard to any proposed or`
  line `existing programme for the promotion and development of the objects of the Foundation, as the Central`
  line `Government may, from time to time, direct.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Foundation shall, as soon as possible`
  line `after the end of each financial year, submit to the Central Government an annual report in such form and`
  line `before such date as may be prescribed, giving a true and full account of its activities and programmes`
  line `during the previous year`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the report received under sub-section (2) shall be laid, as soon as may be, after it is`
  line `received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (3074)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Prior approval of the Central Government for alienation of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3074&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The Foundation shall`
  line `not, except with the previous approval of the Central Government, sell or otherwise dispose of any`
  line `property vested in the Foundation.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (3075)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions to the Foundation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3075&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, if it is satisfied that it is necessary so to do in the public interest, issue, for reasons to be`
  line `recorded and communicated to the Foundation, such directions as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such directions may include directions`
  line `requiring the Foundation--`
  line
  line `(a) to make or amend any regulation within such period as may be specified in the direction; and`
  line
  line `(b) to give priority to the work undertaken or to be undertaken by the Foundation in such manner`
  line `as the Central Government may think fit to specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) Any direction issued under this section shall have effect notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `law for the time being in force or in the memorandum or regulations of the Kalakshetra Society.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (3076)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Dissolution of the Foundation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3076&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification and for`
  line `reasons to be specified therein, dissolve, the Foundation from such date and for such period as may be`
  line `specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing any such notification, the Central Government shall give a reasonable`
  line `opportunity to the Foundation to make representation against the proposed dissolution.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Foundation is dissolved under sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) all members of the Governing Board, Academic Committee and the Finance Committee,`
  line `notwithstanding that the terms of their office had not expired, shall, from the date of dissolution,`
  line `vacate their offices as such members;`
  line
  line `(b) all powers and duties of the Governing Board, Academic Committee and the Finance`
  line `Committee shall, during the period of dissolution, be exercised and performed by such person or`
  line `persons as the Central Government may appoint in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) all properties and assets vested in the Foundation shall, during the period of dissolution, vest in`
  line `the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(d) as soon as the period of dissolution expires, the Foundation shall be reconstituted in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (3077)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3077&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie`
  line `against the Central Government or any officer of that Government or the Foundation or Member or`
  line `Director or any officer of the Foundation for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done`
  line `under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (3078)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title Indemnity.
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3078&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Every Member of the Governing Board, Academic Committee and the Finance`
  line `Committee and the Director of the Foundation shall be indemnified by the Foundation against all losses`
  line `and expenses incurred by them in relation to the discharge of their duties, except such as are caused by`
  line `their wilful act or default.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (3079)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3079&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules for carrying`
  line `out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the allowances to the Members under sub-section (5) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(b) the powers which the Governing Board shall exercise and the functions which it shall`
  line `discharge under sub-section (2) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(c) functions to be performed by the Finance Committee, under clause (iv) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(d) the salary and allowances and other terms and conditions of service of the Director under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(e) the form and the manner in which the budget is to be prepared by the Governing Board under`
  line `section 23;`
  line
  line `(f) the form and the manner in which, and the time at which, the returns, statements and the annual`
  line `report shall be prepared under section 25;`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (3080)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3080&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Foundation may make regulations, not inconsistent this`
  line `Act and the rules made thereunder, for enabling it to discharge its functions under this Act:`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may provide for all or`
  line `any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the management of the properties and funds, affairs and works of the Foundation;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure in regard to transaction of business of the Governing Board and the Academic`
  line `Committee (including quorum at their meetings) and the transaction of business of the Finance`
  line `Committee under sub-section (3) of section 13, sub-section (3) of section 15 and sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 17;`
  line
  line `(c) creation or abolition of posts and the procedure for appointment of the professional,`
  line `administrative and ministerial staff;`
  line
  line `(d) the tenure of office and other terms and conditions of the members of the Academic`
  line `Committee under sub-section (2) of section 15; and`
  line
  line `(e) the maintenance of accounts, registers and other records of the Foundation.`
  line
  line `(3) No regulation made by the Foundation shall have effect until it has been approved by the Central`
  line `Government and published in the Official Gazette, and the Central Government, in approving the`
  line `regulation, may make changes therein which appear to it to be necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (3081)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3081&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is`
  line `in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation, or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule or regulation, should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (3082)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3082&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years, from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (3083)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777&sectionId=3083&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00008_199406_1517807323777
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Kalakshetra Foundation Ordinance, 1993 (Ord. 31 of 1993) is`
  line `hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the Ordinance so repealed,`
  line `shall be deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
